00:11:19.979 --> 00:11:21.180  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] Right.

140
00:11:22.148 --> 00:11:26.252  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, what do you want? Aren't you normally
at prep school right now?

141
00:11:26.318 --> 00:11:30.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] When we were little,

142
00:11:30.289 --> 00:11:32.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
do you remember burying our dog?

143
00:11:32.358 --> 00:11:34.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-If there's anything you remem--
-[Eriko chuckles]

144
00:11:34.927 --> 00:11:36.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I knew it.

145
00:11:37.129 --> 00:11:40.066  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You wouldn't be here without a reason.

146
00:11:43.035 --> 00:11:45.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you seen Kai lately?

147
00:11:46.772 --> 00:11:49.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, I haven't.

148
00:11:50.443 --> 00:11:52.278  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to see him again.

149
00:11:56.882 --> 00:11:59.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Kei] Did you get it, Kai?
-[Kai] Yeah, I got it!

150
00:12:00.319 --> 00:12:04.056  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] Wow, it's a saw-tooth stag beetle!

151
00:12:04.790 --> 00:12:06.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both laughing]

152
00:12:08.160 --> 00:12:11.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei, give me your cell phone.

153
00:12:11.997 --> 00:12:13.099  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] Why?

154
00:12:13.165 --> 00:12:15.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[mother] I'm deleting Kaito's information.

155
00:12:16.001 --> 00:12:17.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
ADDRESS BOOK: KAITO

156
00:12:17.103 --> 00:12:20.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have to choose your friends carefully
if you want to be an upstanding person.

157
00:12:23.843 --> 00:12:26.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You used to be so close.

158
00:12:27.046 --> 00:12:29.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles] I'm kind of busy lately.

159
00:12:29.748 --> 00:12:33.018  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're going
to be someone upstanding after all.

160
00:12:33.085 --> 00:12:35.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, Eri, you really don't remember?

161
00:12:35.788 --> 00:12:38.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-When we buried the dog--
-It's too long ago to remember.

162
00:12:40.092 --> 00:12:43.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you just leave already.
Aren't you busy?

163
00:12:52.304 --> 00:12:55.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[nurse]
Time for your blood draw, Ms. Nagai.

164
00:12:56.308 --> 00:12:58.010  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, they're pretty.

165
00:12:58.077 --> 00:12:59.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Eriko] Just throw them out.

166
00:13:04.316 --> 00:13:06.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>[Kei]</i>
<i>Becoming a fine, upstanding human being.</i>

167
00:13:06.919 --> 00:13:09.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You have to do only what's necessary.</i>

168
00:13:09.889 --> 00:13:11.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Choose only what's necessary.</i>

169
00:13:13.259 --> 00:13:16.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Watanabe] So, I was like-- Oh.

170
00:13:16.295 --> 00:13:17.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nagai!

171
00:13:17.796 --> 00:13:19.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] <i>Anything unnecessary...</i>

172
00:13:19.498 --> 00:13:21.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Watanabe] Uh, Nagai?

173
00:13:21.333 --> 00:13:23.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] <i>has to be cast away.</i>

174
00:13:26.071 --> 00:13:27.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Could that be...?</i>

175
00:13:31.510 --> 00:13:33.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei grunts and tires screeching]

176
00:13:39.285 --> 00:13:40.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[all gasp]

177
00:13:56.335 --> 00:13:59.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[driver] It was a red light.

178
00:13:59.471 --> 00:14:01.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was that kid's fault, right?

179
00:14:01.840 --> 00:14:03.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[man] Was there an accident?

180
00:14:03.509 --> 00:14:04.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gasps]

181
00:14:09.048 --> 00:14:10.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei grunting]

182
00:14:17.189 --> 00:14:19.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei continues grunting]

183
00:14:25.231 --> 00:14:27.032  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei gasping]

184
00:14:34.240 --> 00:14:35.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No!

185
00:14:36.542 --> 00:14:38.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[man 1] An Ajin?
-[man 2] It's an Ajin.

186
00:14:39.011 --> 00:14:41.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Watanabe] They really exist.

187
00:14:41.313 --> 00:14:42.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] No...

188
00:14:42.915 --> 00:14:45.184  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, this isn't...

189
00:14:45.251 --> 00:14:47.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not!

190
00:14:48.053 --> 00:14:51.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is some kind of mistake!

191
00:14:51.156 --> 00:14:53.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm human!

192
00:14:55.961 --> 00:14:57.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Watanabe] Yeah. I believe you.

193
00:14:57.229 --> 00:15:00.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, we're friends after all.

194
00:15:01.433 --> 00:15:04.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Watanabe] ...a massive bounty...
-Ajin aren't human?

195
00:15:04.069 --> 00:15:05.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course not.

196
00:15:06.472 --> 00:15:12.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei screaming]

197
00:15:14.179 --> 00:15:16.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't move. [grunting]

198
00:15:18.050 --> 00:15:19.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't move.

199
00:15:20.252 --> 00:15:21.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei] No.

200
00:15:23.022 --> 00:15:24.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

201
00:15:24.523 --> 00:15:25.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No!

202
00:15:29.595 --> 00:15:31.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[police siren wailing]

203
00:15:31.263 --> 00:15:33.532  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] It wasn't any ordinary accident.

204
00:15:33.599 --> 00:15:35.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was an Ajin.

205
00:15:36.936 --> 00:15:38.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I talk to you for a moment?

206
00:15:38.637 --> 00:15:41.006  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you know someone named Kei Nagai?

207
00:15:43.275 --> 00:15:45.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never heard of him.

208
00:15:46.011 --> 00:15:47.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What'd he do?

209
00:15:47.579 --> 00:15:50.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[woman] Apparently, he's an Ajin.

210
00:15:50.382 --> 00:15:52.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-An Ajin?
-It's true.

211
00:15:52.451 --> 00:15:54.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I saw him come back to life.

212
00:15:54.653 --> 00:15:57.089  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, good for him, I guess.

213
00:15:57.156 --> 00:15:59.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Okay, I just wanted to ask
if you knew him.

214
00:16:03.095 --> 00:16:04.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei.

215
00:16:14.573 --> 00:16:17.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[panting]

216
00:16:20.679 --> 00:16:23.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No way. They're already at my house?

217
00:16:25.451 --> 00:16:28.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Where? Where can I run?

218
00:16:48.707 --> 00:16:49.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
FRIEND 1, 2, 3...

219
00:16:50.042 --> 00:16:52.144  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Somebody, anybody.

220
00:16:52.211 --> 00:16:53.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
ALL CONTACTS:
FRIEND 12, 13...

221
00:16:53.445 --> 00:16:54.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Damn it.

222
00:17:03.222 --> 00:17:04.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kai] <i>Look, Kei!</i>

223
00:17:07.559 --> 00:17:09.094  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai...

224
00:17:10.295 --> 00:17:11.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
KAITO

225
00:17:17.669 --> 00:17:19.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone buzzing]

226
00:17:21.306 --> 00:17:23.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei, I've been waiting for you.

227
00:17:23.642 --> 00:17:25.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai, I...

228
00:17:25.544 --> 00:17:27.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do I do?

229
00:17:28.313 --> 00:17:31.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Calm down. Where are you now?

230
00:17:31.116 --> 00:17:33.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I'm...

231
00:17:34.486 --> 00:17:36.588  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I believe you.

232
00:17:41.226 --> 00:17:42.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei?

233
00:17:44.596 --> 00:17:46.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You can trust me.

234
00:17:46.532 --> 00:17:47.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai.

235
00:17:49.101 --> 00:17:51.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Kei and Kai laughing as kids]

236
00:17:54.306 --> 00:17:57.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Under the tree
where we found that stag beetle.

237
00:17:58.744 --> 00:18:00.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right there.

238
00:18:16.728 --> 00:18:17.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kai?

239
00:18:27.873 --> 00:18:30.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ajin in sight. Requesting backup.

240
00:18:31.243 --> 00:18:33.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, wait! Stop!

241
00:18:38.851 --> 00:18:41.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They're not going to catch me!</i>
<i>No way I'll let them!</i>

242
00:19:04.443 --> 00:19:05.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cop] I'm not going to hurt you.

243
00:19:05.878 --> 00:19:07.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just come out quietly.

244
00:19:18.257 --> 00:19:20.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[gunshot, then Kei gasps]

245
00:19:21.860 --> 00:19:23.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[grunting]

246
00:19:24.429 --> 00:19:27.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't move! Don't you move.

247
00:19:30.302 --> 00:19:32.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've apprehended
the Ajin near Tsuki Shrine.

248
00:19:32.704 --> 00:19:35.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I repeat, I have the Ajin in custody.
-Ajin?

249
00:19:40.846 --> 00:19:42.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[cop grunts]

250
00:19:43.682 --> 00:19:45.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Kai--
-[Kai] Stop!

251
00:19:45.317 --> 00:19:46.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No names.

252
00:19:48.854 --> 00:19:50.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can you stand?

253
00:19:57.229 --> 00:19:58.597  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Time to run.

254
00:20:03.235 --> 00:20:05.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Ajin is on the run!

255
00:20:05.804 --> 00:20:09.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I repeat, the Ajin is on the run!
He seems to have an accomplice.

256
00:20:09.408 --> 00:20:11.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Requesting roadblocks!

257
00:20:16.448 --> 00:20:18.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[Kai] You good?
-Yeah.

258
00:20:27.226 --> 00:20:29.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sirens wailing]

259
00:20:40.939 --> 00:20:42.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[woman on TV]
<i>We are live in front of the Ajin's house.</i>

260
00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:46.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>This is the third Ajin discovery</i>
<i>and fugitive on Japanese soil.</i>

261
00:20:46.478 --> 00:20:49.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>This small town is in an uproar.</i>

262
00:20:49.681 --> 00:20:54.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>I've thought for a long time now</i>
<i>that he didn't seem human.</i>

263
00:20:56.555 --> 00:20:58.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Watanabe speaking inaudibly]

264
00:21:09.468 --> 00:21:11.036  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
AJIN DISCOVERED IN CAR ACCIDENT
THIRD CASE IN JAPAN

265
00:21:19.411 --> 00:21:21.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Araki]
<i>Ajin or not, he's still just a kid!</i>

266
00:21:21.713 --> 00:21:23.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He won't get far.

267
00:21:23.382 --> 00:21:24.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hurry up and nab him.

268
00:21:25.317 --> 00:21:27.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[phone ringing]

269
00:21:27.886 --> 00:21:31.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Thank you for waiting, I'm Araki
from the Saitama Prefectural Police.

270
00:21:31.523 --> 00:21:34.026  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Tosaki]
You're all underestimating the situation.

271
00:21:35.327 --> 00:21:38.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But we have plenty
of men conducting the search--

272
00:21:38.297 --> 00:21:40.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is a national issue.</i>

273
00:21:41.533 --> 00:21:42.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hm.

274
00:21:42.668 --> 00:21:46.571  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every country has seen efforts
to shed light on the Ajins stalled.

275
00:21:46.638 --> 00:21:49.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You are of course aware
what will happen if Kei Nagai

276
00:21:49.975 --> 00:21:53.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is captured by another country
due to your negligence?

277
00:21:59.918 --> 00:22:03.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Double-- No, triple our men!

278
00:22:03.622 --> 00:22:05.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do whatever it takes to bring him in!

279
00:22:06.458 --> 00:22:09.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Kei Nagai, our new Ajin.

280
00:22:10.429 --> 00:22:12.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I won't let you get away.

281
00:22:27.679 --> 00:22:29.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
